    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "HOMEVISION https://www.homevision.co/\n\nMandatory Location: Buenos Aires or Rosario (Argentina)\n\nStack: React, TypeScript\n\nAt HomeVision, we’re modernizing the technology that powers the U.S. home valuation industry. Our platform helps appraisal professionals analyze properties, manage workflows, and produce trusted valuations for a $40 trillion asset class.\n\nBacked by Initialized Capital, we’re building software that replaces legacy tools and spreadsheets with modern, intuitive workflows. Our users spend hours each day in our product, so great interface design and thoughtful frontend engineering directly impact their productivity.\n\nWe’re looking for a Senior Frontend Engineer who cares deeply about product quality, user experience, and maintainable frontend architecture. You’ll play an important role in shaping how our product looks, feels, and evolves as our engineering team grows.\n\nWhat you’ll do:\n\n - Build and ship high-quality product features using React and TypeScript\n\n - Design interfaces that make complex workflows and data understandable and efficient\n\n - Help define and evolve our shared component library and frontend architecture\n\n - Establish and promote best practices for frontend engineering\n\n - Collaborate closely with product managers, designers, and backend engineers\n\n - Mentor and guide other frontend engineers through code reviews and architectural discussions\n\n - Improve performance, usability, and accessibility across the product\n\n - Help adopt and refine AI-assisted development workflows that accelerate engineering productivity\n\nWhat you’ll bring:\n\n - Strong experience building production React applications with TypeScript\n\n - Experience designing maintainable frontend architecture in growing codebases\n\n - Experience building or maintaining shared UI component libraries or design systems\n\n - A track record of raising the bar for frontend quality through code review, mentorship, and technical leadership\n\n - Strong product instincts and empathy for end users\n\n - Ability to take ownership of meaningful product areas and drive them forward\n\n - Comfort collaborating across engineering, product, and design\n\nBonus points:\n\n - Experience building complex user-facing products with rich data or workflows\n\n - Experience improving performance and scalability of large React applications\n\n - Experience with modern frontend tooling and developer experience improvements\n\n - Familiarity with AI-powered development tools such as Copilot, Claude, ChatGPT, or Cursor\n\n - Experience working in high-growth startup environments\n\n\nTHE INTERVIEW PROCESS:\n\n - Silver.dev http://Silver.dev Recruiter Screening\n\n - Hiring Manager Screen\n\n - Take-home Challenge\n\n - Take-home Review\n\n - Live-Coding Interview (if required by the Team)",
